apt-get "program to used to install application"
apt-get install Anyprogram " install is just a action which acts upon Anyprogram" 
we need to remember that this command install app which are located in repository if the app is not present the it will not install any apps 
apt-get remove Anyprogram "this is simply going to remove Anyprogram"
apt-cache search Anyprogram* "this is going to find anything that as a word Anyprogram"
apt-cache policy Anyprogram "this will that if the program is installed in the system and it will show possible link to repository"
dpkg -l ./Anyprogram.deb "this is going to install the app downloaded .deb file"
apt-get upgrade "this is going upgrade all the packages"
